        "subject": "LU-1787 osc: osc_setup doesn't return rc in all cases",
        "message": "LU-1787 osc: osc_setup doesn't return rc in all cases\n\nThe function osc_setup always exits with a rc value. If\nptlrpcd_alloc_work fails in osc_setup the variable rc is\nnot set with the error code but with zero which reports\nsucess which is not the case. The fix is set rc to the\nerror value return from ptlrpcd_alloc_work if it fails.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nChange-Id: I3e3792a52defb5f8c4263ea62b2ea282723e458f\n"
      },
